FBIS3-30875 "dreeu027__a94036" FBIS-EEU-94-027-A Document Type:Daily Report 9 February 1994 ANNEX Slovakia Meciar's Claim of Kovac-HZDS Talks Rejected AU0902145994 Prague CTK in English 2111 GMT 8 Feb 94 AU0902145994 Prague CTK Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Bratislava, Feb 8 (CTK) -- Anton Bodis, a spokesman for Slovak President Michal Kovac, rejected today allegations by Prime Minister Vladimir Meciar that Kovac had negotiated with representatives of the deputies' group of the Meciar-led Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS), urging them to establish factions within the movement. Bodis was reacting to press reports quoting Meciar as saying that "the president is leading consultations (on possible factions within the government coalition HZDS) with some parliamentary deputies, and recommends concrete alternatives." Bodis said that Kovac last met with HZDS deputies at his meeting with all deputies' groups in the parliament late last year.
